HEADWORD: Zein
<hw>Ze"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>z⟦eacute⟧ine</ets>. See <er>Zea</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A nitrogenous substance of the nature of gluten, obtained from the
seeds of Indian corn (<spn>Zea</spn>) as a soft, yellowish, amorphous
substance.</def> <altsp>[Formerly written <asp>zeine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

